'''''Of Minds, Men, and Machines''''' was a [[Book/Legends|book]] by the great [[Pre-Republic era|Pre-Republic]] [[Philosopher/Legends|philosopher]] [[Plaristes]] discussing [[Droid/Legends|droid]] [[Sentience/Legends|sentience]]. The book reached the conclusion that droids were not true sentients since all their feelings and thought were preprogrammed or indirectly the result of programming.

It was referred to in the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Tam Azur-Jamin]]'s treatise ''[[Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena]]''.

